  "prompt": "What is Demand Forecasting and it's methods?",
  "response": "Demand Forecasting is a systematic process of predicting future customer demand for a product or service using historical data and various analytical techniques. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\nDefinition:\n- Predicting future sales and customer demand\n- Helps businesses plan production, inventory, and resource allocation\n- Reduces uncertainties in business planning\n\nMethods of Demand Forecasting:\n\n1. Qualitative Methods:\n- Market Research\n- Expert Opinion\n- Delphi Technique\n- Consumer Survey\n- Sales Force Composite Method\n\n2. Quantitative Methods:\na. Time Series Analysis\n- Moving Average\n- Exponential Smoothing\n- Trend Projection\n- Seasonal Adjustment\n\nb. Causal/Regression Methods:\n- Linear Regression\n- Multiple Regression\n- Econometric Modeling\n- Input-Output Analysis\n\n3. Machine Learning Methods:\n- Neural Networks\n- Decision Trees\n- Support Vector Machines\n- Random Forest\n- Deep Learning Algorithms\n\n4. Statistical Methods:\n- Trend Analysis\n- Correlation Analysis\n- Regression Analysis\n- Probability Distributions\n\n5. Technological Methods:\n- Big Data Analytics\n- Predictive Analytics\n- AI-driven Forecasting\n- Cloud-based Forecasting Tools\n\nBenefits:\n- Improved inventory management\n- Better resource allocation\n- Enhanced production planning\n- Reduced operational costs\n- Improved customer satisfaction",
